    ],
    "text": "Proof Firstly, from ( 9.14 ) we get",
    "reading_order": 2,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "equ",
    "bbox": [
      288,
      230,
      1071,
      423
    ],
    "text": "$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\left|P_{n}-\\sum_{k=1}^{n} \\frac{\\mu(k)}{k^{2}}\\right| & =\\left|\\sum_{k=1}^{n} \\mu(k)\\left(\\frac{1}{n^{2}}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^{2}-\\frac{1}{k^{2}}\\right)\\right| \\\\\n& \\leq \\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\left|\\frac{1}{k^{2}}-\\frac{1}{n^{2}}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^{2}\\right| .\n\\end{aligned}\\quad(9.15)$$",
    "reading_order": 3,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "para",
    "bbox": [
      145,
      455,
      1074,
      520
    ],
    "text": "In order to estimate the last sum above, we claim that, given natural numbers $n$\nand $k$ such that $1 \\leq k \\leq n$ , we have",
    "reading_order": 4,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "equ",
    "bbox": [
      444,
      550,
      774,
      619
    ],
    "text": "$$\\left| { \\frac { 1 } { k ^ { 2 } } } - { \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } } \\left[ { \\frac { n } { k } } \\right] ^ { 2 } \\right| < { \\frac { 2 } { n k } } - { \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } } .$$",
    "reading_order": 5,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "para",
    "bbox": [
      145,
      649,
      234,
      681
    ],
    "text": "Indeed,",
    "reading_order": 6,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "equ",
    "bbox": [
      288,
      712,
      932,
      935
    ],
    "text": "$$\\begin{array} { r l } { \\frac { n } { k } - 1 < \\left\\lfloor \\frac { n } { k } \\right\\rfloor } & { \\leq \\frac { n } { k } \\Rightarrow \\frac { n ^ { 2 } } { k ^ { 2 } } - \\frac { 2 n } { k } + 1 < \\left\\lfloor \\frac { n } { k } \\right\\rfloor ^ { 2 } \\leq \\frac { n ^ { 2 } } { k ^ { 2 } } } \\\\ & { \\Rightarrow \\frac { 1 } { k ^ { 2 } } - \\frac { 2 } { k n } + \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } < \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } \\left\\lfloor \\frac { n } { k } \\right\\rfloor ^ { 2 } \\leq \\frac { 1 } { k ^ { 2 } } } \\\\ & { \\Rightarrow 0 \\leq \\frac { 1 } { k ^ { 2 } } - \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } \\left\\lfloor \\frac { n } { k } \\right\\rfloor ^ { 2 } < \\frac { 2 } { k n } - \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } , } \\end{array}$$",
    "reading_order": 7,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "para",
    "bbox": [
      145,
      962,
      267,
      995
    ],
    "text": "as wished.",
    "reading_order": 8,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "para",
    "bbox": [
      179,
      996,
      799,
      1029
    ],
    "text": "Back to (9.15), we obtain from the above estimates that",
    "reading_order": 9,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "equ",
    "bbox": [
      312,
      1060,
      908,
      1148
    ],
    "text": "$$\\left| P _ { n } - \\sum _ { k = 1 } ^ { n } { \\frac { \\mu ( k ) } { k ^ { 2 } } } \\right| < \\sum _ { k = 1 } ^ { n } \\left( { \\frac { 2 } { n k } } - { \\frac { 1 } { n ^ { 2 } } } \\right) = { \\frac { 2 } { n } } \\sum _ { k = 1 } ^ { n } { \\frac { 1 } { k } } - { \\frac { 1 } { n } } .$$",
    "reading_order": 10,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "para",
    "bbox": [
      145,
      1177,
      533,
      1211
    ],
    "text": "Now, from L'Hôpital's rule we get",
    "reading_order": 11,
    "tags": []
  },
  {
    "label": "equ",
    "bbox": [
      321,
      1244,
      898,
